41
00:02:49,660 --> 00:02:52,020
 My older brother is deaf. 

42
00:03:35,890 --> 00:03:38,210
- Hello! 
 - Hey, Eun Gyeol!

43
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:39,820
- Are you here to eat? 
 - Yeah!

44
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,990
Have a nice day!

45
00:03:42,790 --> 00:03:44,310
- Hi, Eun Gyeol! 
 - Hello!

46
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:46,090
Hey!

47
00:03:47,770 --> 00:03:50,200
   

48
00:03:57,550 --> 00:03:59,330
 (Grab the handles! It's dangerous!) 

49
00:03:59,330 --> 00:04:02,580
 (Don't go so fast, you'll fall!) 

50
00:04:05,170 --> 00:04:08,000
 (Don't do that) 

51
00:04:11,140 --> 00:04:13,910
 My parents are deaf, too. 

52
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:18,430
 But I'm not. 

53
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:20,700
 I can hear. 

54
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,890
 I can speak. 

55
00:04:35,730 --> 00:04:37,750
We need more chicken over here.

56
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,170
Coming right up!

57
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,300
Today's special!

58
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:57,870
Wow, Eun Gyeol!

59
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:59,590
Helping your parents out again today?

60
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:01,800
Gosh, you are such a good kid.

61
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:04,160
- I heard you do well in school, too. 
 - Sort of.

62
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,670
If I had a son like you, I'd gladly raise ten of them.

63
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:09,620
- I agree. 
 - Hold on.

64
00:05:10,290 --> 00:05:11,590
Take it, take it.

65
00:05:11,590 --> 00:05:13,580
No. My dad would get mad at me.

66
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,220
Just take it, kid.

67
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:18,380
Maybe you could bring out two makgeollis?

68
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:21,240
I can't do that. If you're drunk, you'll get into an accident.

69
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,290
Just one glass per person.

70
00:05:23,290 --> 00:05:26,270
But I'll make sure they're strong pours.

71
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:28,700
Got it, kid!

72
00:05:31,380 --> 00:05:33,250
Cabbage delivery!

73
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,840
- Hi! 
 - Hey, Eun Gyeol!

74
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:38,410
Goodness, so busy!

75
00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:41,440
Hello!

76
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:59,020
What? Is something wrong with the delivery?

77
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:01,670
She says to take it back right now.

78
00:06:02,450 --> 00:06:03,630
What did you say?

79
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:07,430
She says if you keep bringing inventory that won't sell, she'll stop working with you.

80
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:09,580
When did I do that?

81
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:29,350
These meals feed people who put in their blood and sweat.

82
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:31,050
She says, don't mess around with the ingredients.

83
00:06:31,050 --> 00:06:33,380
Wow. This is crazy.

84
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:35,350
Who messed with it? Me?

85
00:06:35,350 --> 00:06:37,900
She says just because we can't hear or speak doesn't mean we're stupid.

86
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,650
Don't even think about ripping us off.

87
00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:44,750
She's let it go until now because of my dad, but she won't take it anymore.

88
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:49,150
She'll look at what you bring tomorrow and pay for this month's ingredients.

89
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:52,840
But why does it feel like you're scolding me?

90
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:57,890
The last thing you said. You didn't make that up, did you?

91
