96
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:39,950
 Merry Christmas! 

97
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:41,860
Merry Christmas!

98
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:43,160
 Why did you wake up? 

99
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:48,420
The choir singing and the snow falling woke me up.

100
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:50,950
 I thought snow fell silently. 

101
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:52,800
I can hear it.

102
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,830
 What does it sound like? 

103
00:07:54,830 --> 00:08:00,500
A sound that gives me a warm and fuzzy feeling, like the laundry you dry in the sun.

104
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:04,750
 Snow is cold, but the sound is warm? 

105
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:09,700
 Eun Gyeol, you might grow up to be a poet. 

106
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:19,190
 Oh, it's snowing! 

107
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:22,640
 Let's go outside and make a snowman. 

108
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,970
Brother!

109
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:26,310
Mom! Dad! Mom!

110
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:41,220
Mom! Dad! Brother!

111
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:42,460
That thing's going to fall!

112
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:45,710
It's dangerous! Hurry up!

113
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:29,550
 I told you not to go near buildings under construction. It's dangerous. 

114
00:10:29,550 --> 00:10:32,180
 But Dad saved me. 

115
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:35,720
 What if Eun Gyeol had been next to you? 

116
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:43,230
Dad, if Brother and I are both in danger,

117
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:45,810
who are you going to save first?

118
00:10:46,730 --> 00:10:48,040
Dad!

119
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:51,090
If Brother and I are both in danger,

120
00:10:51,090 --> 00:10:54,160
who are you going to save first?

121
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,870
 Sounds fun. 

122
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:02,270
 If Eun Ho, Eun Gyeol, and I are all in danger? 

123
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:04,960
 Who are you going to save first? 

124
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,900
 I regretted asking that question. 

125
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,800
 Obviously... 

126
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:24,860
 From that day, I remembered my dad's answer at every important moment in my life 

127
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:27,990
 and my heart ached every time. 

128
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:56,590
 What floor are we on? 

129
00:11:59,110 --> 00:12:03,580
   

130
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:19,210
You made it!

131
00:12:20,290 --> 00:12:22,090
Mom, that lady is here.

132
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:24,440
You're early.

133
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:31,560
You know I'm giving you way under the market rate. Right?

134
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:36,780
 The lady says the house is cheap. You know that. Right? 

135
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:41,270
No one in the building liked the idea,

136
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:43,820
but I went door to door to convince them.

137
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:47,290
I told them, at least you won't be loud.

138
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:54,650
I like it quiet and peaceful, and disabled people—

139
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:59,000
I don't have anything against them.

140
00:13:01,310 --> 00:13:03,330
 The lady welcomes us. 

141
00:13:03,330 --> 00:13:05,920
 She says, go on and move in your stuff. 

142
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:09,370
Huh?

143
00:13:11,980 --> 00:13:14,100
Why are your parents laughing at me?

144
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:16,800
You didn't talk trash about me, did you?

145
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:20,300
No. I told them what you said.

146
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:23,620
So why was it so short? I talked for a long time.

147
00:13:23,620 --> 00:13:27,790
If that's all, could I go move our stuff now?

148
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:29,760
Sure, well. Sure!

149
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,890
See you later.

150
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:40,980
   

151
00:13:45,580 --> 00:13:49,910
What in the world? He is different than he looks.

152
00:13:53,890 --> 00:13:57,190
Hey, Byung Ho. Where are you right now?

153
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:10,490
♫  An especially bright, happy day  ♫

154
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:13,830
♫  My heart is beating, you might hear it  ♫

155
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:17,330
♫  I don't want anyone but me to know  ♫

156
00:14:17,330 --> 00:14:20,550
♫  You don't know how I feel  ♫

157
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:24,040
♫  I feel weird when I look at you  ♫

158
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:27,890
♫  Did I find the universe I lost?  ♫

159
00:14:27,890 --> 00:14:34,250
♫  I'm so curious, the story of you and me  ♫

160
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:41,920
♫  Tell me. Do you feel the way I do sometimes?  ♫

161
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:51,150
♫  You can tell me that you feel the same way, too  ♫

162
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:03,590
 We're going to be coming home late often. 

163
00:15:03,590 --> 00:15:07,490
 If something happens, call us right away. Okay? 

164
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:15,410
 After school, come to the restaurant to have lunch. 

165
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:18,400
You'll pack us dinner, so we'll bring it home to eat.

166
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,490
Don't ever touch the gas stove.

167
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:22,230
Right?

168
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:25,040
 After sunset, come home... 

169
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,600
I'll always stay with Brother, no matter what.

170
00:15:29,390 --> 00:15:31,450
 I need to go right now. 

171
00:15:31,450 --> 00:15:34,060
 Do I need to go to the bathroom with him, too? 

172
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:55,480
 Hello, my name is Yeom Byeong Ho. I live on the 4th floor with my mom, the landlady. 

173
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:58,840
 My mom told me to say hello. 

174
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:02,880
 - Okay. 
 - Hi! 

175
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:05,100
Are you Ha Eun Gyeol?

176
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:09,410
Can I go play with Eun Gyeol?

177
00:16:09,410 --> 00:16:12,340
I want to show him around the neighborhood.

178
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:16,020
 Of course, of course. 

179
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:18,440
Can my brother come?

180
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:22,450
 My mom told me to be friends with just you since you get good grades— 

181
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:26,640
Today is just for fourth graders.

182
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:29,870
Let's hang out with your brother next time.

183
00:16:29,870 --> 00:16:31,920
Is that okay?

184
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:34,190
 Of course. 

185
00:16:46,410 --> 00:16:49,520
   

186
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,390
Why are we stopping?

187
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:54,210
You should know.

188
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:58,230
You always avoid that place.

189
00:16:58,230 --> 00:17:00,360
   

190
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:04,350
I heard the old guy who runs that store eats children.

191
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:08,570
Do you actually believe that?

192
00:17:08,570 --> 00:17:11,160
This guy can't follow a joke.

193
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:13,350
What we mean is,

194
00:17:15,820 --> 00:17:19,000
he wears a special bracelet right here.

195
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,630
   

196
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,950
   

197
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:55,190
Hold on!

198
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:56,830
Get it! Please!

199
00:17:56,830 --> 00:18:00,300
- No, no, no, no! 
 - Eat, eat. Hurry.

200
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,360
Hurry up, hurry up.

201
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:04,300
   

202
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:06,100
Eat, eat!

203
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:08,000
    
 Is there more?

204
00:18:08,010 --> 00:18:10,390
No, no, right there!

205
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:14,010
Next to you! No, in front of you!

206
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:16,170
What are you doing?

207
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:19,680
 Eun Gyeol, come home right now! 

208
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:22,090
Why? I'm having fun.

209
00:18:22,090 --> 00:18:25,290
Hey! What are you doing with the charger? The center is wide open.

210
00:18:25,290 --> 00:18:27,880
Gosh! I died.

211
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:32,590
 Mom and I need to go to the restaurant. 

212
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:35,550
 Your brother is going to be alone. 

213
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:37,080
 Hurry home right now. 

214
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:39,120
Okay.

215
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:44,030
Sorry, guys. I need to go home.

216
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:47,560
What was he doing on his phone?

217
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:48,610
Sign language.

218
00:18:48,610 --> 00:18:51,100
It's creepy. Don't bring him along next time.

219
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:53,230
Deal with it.

220
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:56,160
I'll put him to good use later.

221
00:18:56,930 --> 00:18:59,550
 You guys remember tomorrow is the math chapter test. Right? 

222
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:01,160
 Yes! 

223
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:06,160
The test will cover multiplication to division.

224
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:09,070
Please try your best to be ready.

225
00:19:09,070 --> 00:19:11,010
 Yes! 

226
00:19:11,010 --> 00:19:13,050
- Hey, Ha Eun Gyeol. 
 - Yes?

227
00:19:13,050 --> 00:19:17,600
Maybe you can be polite this time and get one question wrong?

228
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,700
You know I'm kidding. Right?

229
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,710
- Yeom Byeong Ho! 
 - Yes?

230
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:26,650
Maybe you can be polite this time and get one question. Right?

231
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:29,860
You know I totally mean that. Right?

232
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:41,310
Want to study for the test together?

233
00:19:41,310 --> 00:19:44,910
Why would we both study? That's unproductive.

234
00:19:44,910 --> 00:19:46,700
Only you need to study.

235
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,300
Hey, Yeom Byeong Ho!

236
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:51,290
The guys we crushed yesterday want revenge. What do you say?

237
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:52,680
We got to fight them, then.

238
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:54,950
Okay, let's go.

239
00:19:54,950 --> 00:19:57,600
Put it in my room.

240
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,640
Hey, what did you mean by that earlier?

241
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,640
Darn it.

242
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,820
I thought you were supposed to be smart.

243
00:20:03,820 --> 00:20:05,550
It's simple, so listen up.

244
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:07,700
Write my name on your test tomorrow.

245
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,450
Then I'll write your name on mine.

246
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:11,680
Super easy. Right?

247
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,320
You want to defraud? 
  (He uses a difficult word for "cheating" here) 

248
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:16,290
I don't know what that means, but do your best. Okay?

249
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:19,210
Don't forget, your family's future depends on you.

250
00:20:19,210 --> 00:20:21,630
My family's future?

251
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:24,900
How much more do I need to beat around the bush?

252
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:30,300
Don't piss off the landlady's son and have your poor family on the streets.

253
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,120
   

254
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:42,680
Five more minutes, guys. Wrap it up.

255
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:46,000
   

256
00:21:02,190 --> 00:21:05,940
   

257
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:14,060
Are you trying to show off or something?

258
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:17,810
I hung out with you out of pity, and you think you're all that?

259
00:21:17,810 --> 00:21:19,970
Don't stare at me.

260
00:21:19,970 --> 00:21:22,280
You want to get beaten up?

261
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:24,040
I never said I'd cooperate.

262
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:26,980
"I never said I'd cooperate."

263
00:21:28,930 --> 00:21:30,890
I'll let it go today.

264
00:21:30,890 --> 00:21:32,680
- But next time, I'll tell your mom— 
 - You jerk!

265
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:33,960
